# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BRIAPI SIT Validator — Environment Variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The server loads .env automatically at startup (existing OS env vars take
# precedence over values in this file, so CI/CD secrets are never overridden).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to the YAML rules file (default: config/rules.yaml)
# CONFIG_PATH=config/rules.yaml


# ── Google Drive Integration (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# When all three GOOGLE_* credentials below are set, every Excel validation
# report is automatically uploaded to your Google Drive.  The Drive view URL
# is returned in the X-Drive-File-URL response header.
#
# First-time setup — run the helper script once to obtain a refresh token:
#   go run scripts/get-drive-token/main.go
#
# See README.md › "Google Drive Integration" for the full walkthrough.

# OAuth2 Client ID from Google Cloud Console
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com

# OAuth2 Client Secret from Google Cloud Console
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

# Long-lived refresh token obtained by running scripts/get-drive-token/main.go
GOOGLE_REFRESH_TOKEN=your-refresh-token

# (Optional) Google Drive folder ID to upload reports into.
# Leave blank to save files to your Drive root.
# Find the ID in the folder's URL: drive.google.com/drive/folders/<FOLDER_ID>
# GOOGLE_DRIVE_FOLDER_ID=
